The IEC values of BCH were measured with the titration method according to a previous study [63]. The BCH membranes were soaked in a 1.0 M NaCl solution for 24 h at ambient temperature to ensure the proton were replaced completely by the sodium ion. This solution was subsequently titrated against a 0.005 M sodium hydroxide solution to neutralize the exchanged protons using phenolphthalein as an indicator. After that, the calculated IEC value was obtained through Eq. (1).1IEC=a×bm\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
