				\usepackage{mathrsfs}
				\usepackage{upgreek}
				\setlength{\oddsidemargin}{-69pt}
				\begin{document}$${\text{IEC}} = \,\,\frac{a\, \times \,b}{m}$$\end{document}
where IEC is the ion exchange capacity (mmol g−1); a is the added titrant volume at the equivalent point (mL); b is the molar concentration of the titrant; m is the dry membrane weight (g).

BCH membranes samples were removed from storage, the surface water was gently removed using paper filter, and then the wet mass was determined using an analytical balance. Next, BCH membranes samples were dried overnight at 50 °C in an oven, to completely remove water and then weighted again. The moisture content percentage (W%) was calculated using Eq. (2) [28].2W(\% )=wwet-wdrywdry×100\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
